column1:
Unisex watches have a certain quality about them; neither are they too dainty nor too rugged mainly because they have to suit the needs of both men and women. Such watches are also perfect for those women who do not prefer girly accessories or too vivid colors. Wear this unisex Timex Analog watch with a T-shirt and your favorite pair of jeans and be the epitome of understated style.

Body and Design

This analog watch from Timex sports a round dial that looks good on both male and female wrists. The time is marked on the face of the watch with full Arabic numerals and tiny lines denote the minutes. Not only does it look tasteful
column2: it also gives the watch an aura of precision. Are you tired of metal straps that feel cold on your hurt and start chafing when used for extended periods of time? This Timex analog model has a gorgeous brown leather strap that breathes and keeps the skin warm in winter as well. For an accessory that is in constant use
column3: it is very important for the watch to be snug and comfortable; this watch fulfills that requirement perfectly.

column1: In this fast-paced world
column2: you are not left with much time to attend to little things like polishing your watch with wax and buffing out scratches from the watch case. This Timex analog unisex watch has a brass case surrounding the dial which is extremely easy to clean; just brush your watch with a clean cloth and restore the shine to it. Brass not only adds a cheery look to the watch but also is more economic.

column1: Boiling an egg can be fun with this watch that has a ring that turns in one direction. This is a simplified form of a tachymeter that can be used to calculate elapsed time. Set the mark where the minute hand is right now; when it reaches 10
column2:
your egg is done. Burning your cake because you were watching television can be a bummer; ensure that it never happens again with this watch from Timex.

Functions and Other Features

column1: Watching a movie at a drive-in theatre can be quite an experience but the complete darkness that is synonymous to drive-ins can be disconcerting. The Indiglo Night-light technology of this Timex analog watch is almost like magic - press a button and the dial lights up. Not only can you check the time
column2: you can also use the emitted light to find your keys or open the dashboard. This technology
column4: is a form of electroluminescence which is very efficient and can prove useful when you have to open the car door on a late night without a street light.

column1: Need to book tickets for your mother for Saturday? Know the exact date and day at a moment’s notice with the inbuilt day and date display on this watch. The quick date feature also makes it easy to prepare for the week ahead and organize your work on time. Spend your sundays lazing in the pool or surf up a storm at the beach with zero concern about water damage to the watch. This Timex Analog Unisex watch is water resistant and has a water diving depth of 100 m; pump some adrenaline into your veins and give river rafting a go for this watch is very resilient.

column1: Belonging to Timex’s immensely popular and specialized series of Expedition Combo watches is the T49826 analog-digital timepiece. This highly rated timepiece features an analog style display with the inclusion of a slightly less prominent digital display
column2: making it a crossover model with a perfect combination of highly useful technologies.

column1: Built to reflect a certain rugged
column3: this dual technology watch can be used across a multitude of places
column4: occasions and climatic conditions. As a unisex watch
column5:
this T49826 from Timex is designed and styled to be worn by both men and women. This crossover design successfully combines all the fine elements of the great outdoors along with a sense of style and sophistication.

Body & Design

column1: Particularly designed with great amount of importance given to the all-weather functionality of this highly complex timepiece
column2: the T49826 features a bold round dial and watch face. This all important dial is protected by a strong and sturdy resin casing that runs around the entire curve of the glass. This protective casing on the outside of the glass has very prominent markings of the key time positions which alternate starting from the 12 O’clock position all the way around.

column1: This highly capable timepiece is fastened onto your wrist by a very classy and elegant IP Ruthenium Bracelet that matches the colour of the dial. This use of Ruthenium gives the watch amazing strength and a great heat resistance which proves extremely useful considering the outdoor applications of this Expedition series watches.
Multi-functionality being the key aspect of this watch
column2: this Timex T49826 features nothing less than 4 push buttons and a rotating crown which are neatly distributed around the protective fibre case. The rotating crown lets you change or set the correct time
column3: while the 4 push buttons are evenly distributed around the watch’s casing with 2 on the left and 2 on the right and are used to operate the <strong>alarm
column5:
mode and indiglo functionalities.

Functions & Other Features

column1: Perfectly suited for outdoor activities like hiking
column4: this Timex Expedition combo watch provides you with the best of both worlds with its ability to flawlessly combine digital and analog functionalities into one super-efficient and multifunctional personal timekeeper. This Timex Expedition watch from Timex comes loaded with a considerable assortment of highly efficient and immensely useful functions including an analog/digital chronograph and a 24-hour countdown timer.

column1: The analog and digital type displays on this Timex T49826 gives you the ability to read the time using the watch arms or using the digital display. The chronograph function on this watch further comes with an extremely accurate stopwatch with multiple split or lap time feature. This stopwatch with lap or split timers comes in immensely handy for those involved in any field where the accuracy of even the tiniest measure of time counts.

The digital display gives you the option to choose between the 12 and 24-hour time format according to whichever suits you best. This super-efficient and multifunctional timepiece from Timex further comes with the inclusion of an alarm clock function. The alarm can be set and be seen on the digital display that works using the standard beep alarm tone.

This T49826 from Timex has features a highly functional night mode that operates using Timex’s trademark INDIGLO lighting technology that illuminates both the analogue face and the digital display. The water-resistant feature on this watch gives it a maximum operational depth of 50 m which makes sure that water seepage or the subsurface pressure build-up doesn’t affect the watch’s normal functionality. In total
column2: this Timex Expedition watch makes an ideal buy
column3: giving you great aesthetics and practicality with an elevated degree of protection and reliability even against some of the highly unpredictable elements of nature.

column1: Belonging to Timex’s immensely popular and specialized series of Expedition Combo watches is the T49826 analog-digital timepiece. This highly rated timepiece features an analog style display with the inclusion of a slightly less prominent digital display
column2: making it a crossover model with a perfect combination of highly useful technologies.

column1: Built to reflect a certain rugged
column3: this dual technology watch can be used across a multitude of places
column4: occasions and climatic conditions. As a unisex watch
column5:
this T49826 from Timex is designed and styled to be worn by both men and women. This crossover design successfully combines all the fine elements of the great outdoors along with a sense of style and sophistication.

Body & Design

column1: Particularly designed with great amount of importance given to the all-weather functionality of this highly complex timepiece
column2: the T49826 features a bold round dial and watch face. This all important dial is protected by a strong and sturdy resin casing that runs around the entire curve of the glass. This protective casing on the outside of the glass has very prominent markings of the key time positions which alternate starting from the 12 O’clock position all the way around.

column1: This highly capable timepiece is fastened onto your wrist by a very classy and elegant IP Ruthenium Bracelet that matches the colour of the dial. This use of Ruthenium gives the watch amazing strength and a great heat resistance which proves extremely useful considering the outdoor applications of this Expedition series watches.
Multi-functionality being the key aspect of this watch
column2: this Timex T49826 features nothing less than 4 push buttons and a rotating crown which are neatly distributed around the protective fibre case. The rotating crown lets you change or set the correct time
column3: while the 4 push buttons are evenly distributed around the watch’s casing with 2 on the left and 2 on the right and are used to operate the <strong>alarm
column5:
mode and indiglo functionalities.

Functions & Other Features

column1: Perfectly suited for outdoor activities like hiking
column4: this Timex Expedition combo watch provides you with the best of both worlds with its ability to flawlessly combine digital and analog functionalities into one super-efficient and multifunctional personal timekeeper. This Timex Expedition watch from Timex comes loaded with a considerable assortment of highly efficient and immensely useful functions including an analog/digital chronograph and a 24-hour countdown timer.

column1: The analog and digital type displays on this Timex T49826 gives you the ability to read the time using the watch arms or using the digital display. The chronograph function on this watch further comes with an extremely accurate stopwatch with multiple split or lap time feature. This stopwatch with lap or split timers comes in immensely handy for those involved in any field where the accuracy of even the tiniest measure of time counts.

The digital display gives you the option to choose between the 12 and 24-hour time format according to whichever suits you best. This super-efficient and multifunctional timepiece from Timex further comes with the inclusion of an alarm clock function. The alarm can be set and be seen on the digital display that works using the standard beep alarm tone.

This T49826 from Timex has features a highly functional night mode that operates using Timex’s trademark INDIGLO lighting technology that illuminates both the analogue face and the digital display. The water-resistant feature on this watch gives it a maximum operational depth of 50 m which makes sure that water seepage or the subsurface pressure build-up doesn’t affect the watch’s normal functionality. In total
column2: this Timex Expedition watch makes an ideal buy
column3: giving you great aesthetics and practicality with an elevated degree of protection and reliability even against some of the highly unpredictable elements of nature.

column1: From the highly revered and reputed Expedition series of sports and adventure timepieces from Timex is this MF13 analog-digital watch. Carrying the Expedition series’ trademark rugged feel and well protected casing
column2: this Timex Expedition Combo MF13 timepiece features an analog style display with the inclusion of a less prominent digital display
column3: making it a crossover model with a winning combination of useful technologies.

column1: As a unisex watch
column2:
the MF13 is designed and styled to be worn and used by both men and women. This very noticeable hybrid design sense successfully combines all the fine elements of the rough outdoors along with a sense of refinement and sophistication. This makes it the ideal choice for a multitude of occasions ranging from mountain-climbing and kayaking to casual birthday bashes or official conferences.

Body & Design

column1: Purposefully designed with the priority firmly on the all-weather functionality of this highly complex instrument
column2: the MF13 features a bold round watch face. This all-important watch face is protected by a strong and sturdy double layered resin casing that runs around the perimeter of the glass. This rugged looking fibre case also doubles as the watch’s compass directional ring with the 4 directions and the degrees in between them clearly marked and engraved
column3: making sure that you have a steady heading on all of your outdoor adventures.

column1: This highly capable timepiece is fastened onto your wrist by a very classy
column2: smart and rugged looking rubber or a genuine leather fast wrap strap with Timex’s Expedition branding etched on the visible side of the strap. The fastening or unfastening of this visual inspiring timepiece from your wrist is carried out using the watch’s strap clasp type which features a highly stylized metal buckle.

column1: Being a highly multi-functional watch
column2:
the Timex MF13 features nothing less than 4 push buttons and a rotating crown which are neatly distributed around the protective fibre case.

Functions & Other Features

column1: Perfect for military use
column5: this Timex Expedition combo watch provides you with the best of both worlds with its seamless ability to combine digital and analog functionalities into one flawless multi-function timepiece.

column1: This Timex Expedition watch from Timex comes loaded with a considerable assortment of highly efficient and immensely useful functions including 24-hour chronograph
column2: 24-hour countdown timer and 2 time zones.

column1: The combination of analog and digital displays on this Timex MF13 watch gives you dual time display. This means you can read the time using the watch arms or using the digital display. The digital panel can display the time from your preferred alternative time zone while also displaying the progress of the 24-hour countdown timer.

The chronograph function on this watch further comes with an extremely accurate stopwatch with multiple split or lap time feature. This stopwatch with lap or split timers comes in immensely handy for those involved in track and field or motor racing events where knowing and recording multiple split timings is crucial.

The digital display gives you the option to choose between the 12 and 24-hour time format according to whichever suits you best. This super-efficient and multifunctional timepiece from Timex further comes with the inclusion of an alarm clock function. The alarm can be set and be seen on the digital display that works using the beep alarm tone.

This MF13 from Timex has the superlative advantage with a night mode that operates using Timex’s trademark INDIGLO lighting technology that illuminates both the analogue face and the digital display. The water-resistant feature on this watch gives it a maximum operational depth of 50 which makes sure that water seepage or the subsurface pressure build-up don’t affect the watch’s normal functionality. In total
column2: this incredible timepiece from Timex makes a great buy
column3: giving you great aesthetic value and practicality offering a high degree of protection and reliability even when exposed to the forces of nature.
